1
00:00:01,735 --> 00:00:03,937
Knuckle:
Your signature technique

2
00:00:03,971 --> 00:00:07,942
currently has
exactly two major flaws!

3
00:00:07,975 --> 00:00:09,076
Killua: Huh?

4
00:00:14,982 --> 00:00:15,950
♪

5
00:00:15,983 --> 00:00:17,985
( Singing in Japanese )

6
00:00:59,426 --> 00:01:01,428
♪

7
00:01:06,033 --> 00:01:08,536
Narrator: Gon has
finally challenged knuckle

8
00:01:08,569 --> 00:01:10,337
to a serious fight.

9
00:01:10,370 --> 00:01:15,809
However, knuckle claims that
gon’s technique has major flaws.

10
00:01:19,680 --> 00:01:21,048
Knuckle: So, gon...

11
00:01:21,081 --> 00:01:22,282
Gon: Huh?

12
00:01:22,316 --> 00:01:24,351
Knuckle: That technique
you’re using,

13
00:01:24,384 --> 00:01:25,652
what is it you call it?

14
00:01:25,686 --> 00:01:29,290
Gon: Uh-oh! I forgot
to give my attack a name.

15
00:01:29,323 --> 00:01:31,292
What should it be?

16
00:01:31,325 --> 00:01:33,494
It’s ja-jan Ken!

17
00:01:33,527 --> 00:01:35,763
Killua: Wow. Zero effort.

18
00:01:35,796 --> 00:01:38,165
Knuckle: Ah.

19
00:01:38,198 --> 00:01:40,367
Ja-jan Ken, huh?

20
00:01:40,400 --> 00:01:41,701
Okay. I see.

21
00:01:41,735 --> 00:01:44,471
So it’s just like
rock, paper, scissors,

22
00:01:44,505 --> 00:01:47,575
but the "ja-jan" adds
a little oomph, like a "ta-da."

23
00:01:47,608 --> 00:01:50,244
Gon: Well, not really.

24
00:01:50,277 --> 00:01:53,480
( Thinking )the first "ja"
was actually a stutter.

25
00:01:53,514 --> 00:01:55,216
♪

26
00:01:55,249 --> 00:01:58,319
Knuckle: That’s a clever name
you’ve got there, kid!

27
00:01:58,352 --> 00:02:01,155
Gon: Uh, yeah.
I’m okay with that.

28
00:02:01,188 --> 00:02:02,289
Killua: You are?

29
00:02:02,322 --> 00:02:04,124
Knuckle: Well, gon...

30
00:02:04,157 --> 00:02:07,761
Your jajanken
has two giant weaknesses.

31
00:02:07,794 --> 00:02:10,397
First off,
the windup’s too long!

32
00:02:10,430 --> 00:02:11,798
( Gon grunts )

33
00:02:11,832 --> 00:02:13,567
Knuckle: Those few
precious seconds

34
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:15,335
you’re taking before the move

35
00:02:15,369 --> 00:02:17,471
is like an eternity
in actual combat,

36
00:02:17,504 --> 00:02:21,174
so you ain’t gonna get many
chances to use it, will you?

37
00:02:21,208 --> 00:02:22,609
Gon: Yeah, I know that.

38
00:02:22,643 --> 00:02:25,246
Knuckle: And second,
it’s too risky!

39
00:02:25,279 --> 00:02:26,680
( Gon gasps )

40
00:02:26,713 --> 00:02:29,482
Knuckle: See, the more aura
you focus into your fist,

41
00:02:29,516 --> 00:02:31,752
the less you have
at your disposal,

42
00:02:31,785 --> 00:02:34,454
and that’s less that you’ll have
to protect your body!

43
00:02:34,488 --> 00:02:38,225
If someone attacks when
you’re vulnerable, you’re dead!

44
00:02:38,258 --> 00:02:40,527
Gon: I know what the risks are.

45
00:02:40,561 --> 00:02:43,264
That’s why I spent
the last month training,

46
00:02:43,297 --> 00:02:45,166
to make up for them!

47
00:02:45,199 --> 00:02:48,235
♪

48
00:02:48,268 --> 00:02:50,303
Knuckle: Now that
I see it again,

49
00:02:50,337 --> 00:02:52,272
his aura’s really something.

50
00:02:52,306 --> 00:02:55,810
He’s got as much volume
as a mid-ranking pro.

51
00:02:55,843 --> 00:02:57,745
He’s close.

52
00:03:00,714 --> 00:03:03,650
But there’s one thing
he still lacks...

53
00:03:03,684 --> 00:03:04,752
( Gon groans )

54
00:03:04,785 --> 00:03:06,253
Knuckle: Experience!

55
00:03:08,288 --> 00:03:09,856
( Gon yells )

56
00:03:09,890 --> 00:03:12,659
Knuckle: He needs to see
more real combat...

57
00:03:14,161 --> 00:03:15,663
A lot more!

58
00:03:18,699 --> 00:03:21,335
He’s got plenty
of determination,

59
00:03:21,368 --> 00:03:25,672
he’s faced death many times,
and he has natural talent,

60
00:03:25,706 --> 00:03:29,276
but still, he needs work.

61
00:03:30,477 --> 00:03:33,180
His flow of aura’s
still unrefined.

62
00:03:34,715 --> 00:03:36,550
I can tell what he’s protecting,

63
00:03:36,583 --> 00:03:38,785
and I know
what he’s planning to do...

64
00:03:39,820 --> 00:03:42,790
Just by looking at his aura!

65
00:03:45,626 --> 00:03:50,598
So if I use that information
and mix in a few feints...

66
00:03:53,233 --> 00:03:55,802
And stagger my blows a little...

67
00:04:06,446 --> 00:04:08,648
This is the result!

68
00:04:11,451 --> 00:04:12,819
Killua: Damn it.

69
00:04:12,853 --> 00:04:15,723
He’s reading gon’s flow of aura
like a book.

70
00:04:18,759 --> 00:04:22,529
Gon: I was right. Knuckle is...

71
00:04:23,630 --> 00:04:24,931
Knuckle: Okay.

72
00:04:24,965 --> 00:04:28,535
Now I think it’s time
to throw a real punch.

73
00:04:28,569 --> 00:04:30,337
Gon: He’s so...

74
00:04:30,370 --> 00:04:34,207
Knuckle: Don’t blame me
if you die, all right?

75
00:04:34,241 --> 00:04:36,343
Gon: He’s so kind!

76
00:04:36,376 --> 00:04:38,345
Knuckle: Behind you!

77
00:04:40,781 --> 00:04:42,449
( Gon groans )

78
00:04:42,482 --> 00:04:45,652
If he hadn’t warned me,
I could have died.

79
00:04:45,686 --> 00:04:49,857
Knuckle: First off,
the windup’s too long!

80
00:04:49,890 --> 00:04:52,292
Gon: He doesn’t
have to teach me,

81
00:04:52,326 --> 00:04:56,430
but still,
he keeps giving me advice.

82
00:04:56,463 --> 00:05:00,233
He’s guiding me,
teaching me how to get stronger.

83
00:05:02,903 --> 00:05:04,638
He’s being too nice.

84
00:05:07,307 --> 00:05:08,275
Knuckle: Eh?

85
00:05:08,308 --> 00:05:10,777
Gon: Okay, now show me rock.

86
00:05:10,811 --> 00:05:12,513
( Yells )

87
00:05:12,546 --> 00:05:14,314
( Knuckle groans )

88
00:05:22,356 --> 00:05:24,358
♪

89
00:05:25,359 --> 00:05:26,627
( Gon groaning )

90
00:05:26,660 --> 00:05:28,529
( Coughs )

91
00:05:28,562 --> 00:05:31,832
Knuckle: Didn’t I tell you
I wouldn’t let you do that?!

92
00:05:31,865 --> 00:05:33,333
Are you messing with me?

93
00:05:33,367 --> 00:05:37,338
Gon: Was that all you got?

94
00:05:37,371 --> 00:05:38,472
Knuckle: Eh?

95
00:05:39,740 --> 00:05:41,875
Gon: Who’s messing with who?

96
00:05:41,909 --> 00:05:44,345
This is a real fight, isn’t it?

97
00:05:44,378 --> 00:05:47,748
So act like it! Fight to kill!

98
00:05:47,781 --> 00:05:50,884
♪

99
00:05:50,918 --> 00:05:54,021
Show me...

100
00:05:54,054 --> 00:05:56,657
Rock!

101
00:05:56,690 --> 00:05:58,458
( Knuckle gasps )

102
00:06:02,429 --> 00:06:03,463
Gon: Here goes!

103
00:06:04,898 --> 00:06:05,866
Jan...

104
00:06:05,899 --> 00:06:08,869
( Knuckle yells )

105
00:06:10,070 --> 00:06:11,071
Gon: Over here!

106
00:06:17,778 --> 00:06:20,381
All right, now show me rock!

107
00:06:20,414 --> 00:06:21,782
Jan...

108
00:06:32,392 --> 00:06:34,861
( Gasps )

109
00:06:36,897 --> 00:06:38,832
Knuckle: That little bastard,

110
00:06:38,866 --> 00:06:41,569
he faked me out
with his jajanken!

111
00:06:43,036 --> 00:06:45,839
Gon: You were focused on
stopping my special technique.

112
00:06:45,873 --> 00:06:48,476
Even I could tell
exactly how and when

113
00:06:48,509 --> 00:06:50,578
you were about to strike
with your right.

114
00:06:50,611 --> 00:06:52,446
♪

115
00:06:52,479 --> 00:06:53,981
Killua: He used
jajanken’s weakness,

116
00:06:54,014 --> 00:06:56,517
the long windup,
to his advantage.

117
00:06:56,550 --> 00:06:58,719
He’s messing
with the enemy’s mind.

118
00:07:00,787 --> 00:07:02,522
From knuckle’s perspective,

119
00:07:02,556 --> 00:07:04,725
gon’s jajanken
is an easy pitch.

120
00:07:04,758 --> 00:07:06,927
He can’t help but take a swing.

121
00:07:06,960 --> 00:07:10,096
It’s straight down the middle,
and he’s gotta hit it.

122
00:07:11,131 --> 00:07:12,833
That’s the trigger.

123
00:07:12,866 --> 00:07:16,002
As the ball approaches,
he exerts too much strength.

124
00:07:17,137 --> 00:07:18,805
He can hit it. He has to,

125
00:07:18,839 --> 00:07:20,541
and thinking that way

126
00:07:20,574 --> 00:07:23,410
makes him use more muscle
than necessary.

127
00:07:23,443 --> 00:07:26,112
The same thing goes for aura.

128
00:07:26,146 --> 00:07:29,049
Unless it’s
consciously held back,

129
00:07:29,082 --> 00:07:31,051
aura focuses where he tenses up,

130
00:07:31,084 --> 00:07:34,821
and it balloons
the moment he tries to strike.

131
00:07:34,855 --> 00:07:38,092
If the nen user is inexperienced
or loses his cool,

132
00:07:38,125 --> 00:07:42,863
the aura will either stagnate
or, conversely, flow too freely.

133
00:07:43,964 --> 00:07:45,566
The flow of aura
tells the opponent

134
00:07:45,599 --> 00:07:47,734
what attack is coming.

135
00:07:47,768 --> 00:07:51,171
Gon: So act like it!
Fight to kill!

136
00:07:51,205 --> 00:07:53,741
Killua: Gon pointed out
knuckle’s soft side

137
00:07:53,774 --> 00:07:57,745
to upset him,
which made the feint successful.

138
00:07:58,979 --> 00:08:00,647
This plan is more effective

139
00:08:00,681 --> 00:08:03,751
on someone who knows
jajanken’s strength.

140
00:08:03,784 --> 00:08:08,055
As soon as gon initiates
the attack, fear sets in.

141
00:08:08,088 --> 00:08:09,957
The knowledge
of what’s coming next

142
00:08:09,990 --> 00:08:12,960
really messes
with his opponent’s mind.

143
00:08:12,993 --> 00:08:15,762
It makes the feint
more effective.

144
00:08:15,796 --> 00:08:17,164
If they jump back,

145
00:08:17,197 --> 00:08:19,933
then gon can easily
use scissors or paper.

146
00:08:21,201 --> 00:08:23,870
I assumed jajanken
would be less useful

147
00:08:23,904 --> 00:08:26,607
once the opponent
figured out how it works,

148
00:08:26,640 --> 00:08:29,176
that it was flawed.

149
00:08:29,209 --> 00:08:33,680
But, no, he can adapt it
to any situation.

150
00:08:33,714 --> 00:08:35,783
Gon: Right.
Now let’s start over!

151
00:08:35,816 --> 00:08:38,752
Killua: In the second attempt,
gon was too focused

152
00:08:38,785 --> 00:08:40,987
on the technique,
and knuckle landed a kick.

153
00:08:41,021 --> 00:08:42,823
But if he learns
to control his aura

154
00:08:42,856 --> 00:08:44,825
in response
to his opponent’s moves,

155
00:08:44,858 --> 00:08:46,793
it’ll be harder to distinguish

156
00:08:46,827 --> 00:08:48,829
between the feints
and the real thing.

157
00:08:51,031 --> 00:08:55,002
So then, did gon know
how to overcome this weakness?

158
00:08:58,739 --> 00:09:00,007
No.

159
00:09:00,040 --> 00:09:04,811
He must have figured it out
during the fight.

160
00:09:04,845 --> 00:09:07,715
Even in the middle
of intense combat,

161
00:09:07,748 --> 00:09:10,217
he’s making
incredible progress.

162
00:09:11,251 --> 00:09:14,521
( Gon panting )

163
00:09:14,555 --> 00:09:18,192
It’s already getting
a lot harder to maintain Ken,

164
00:09:18,225 --> 00:09:21,628
and it hasn’t even
been 20 minutes.

165
00:09:21,662 --> 00:09:25,766
I’m using more energy, because
i’m moving at the same time,

166
00:09:25,799 --> 00:09:30,137
and if an hour of training
equals ten minutes of combat...

167
00:09:30,170 --> 00:09:33,640
I’ve only got ten minutes
of aura left!

168
00:09:34,875 --> 00:09:36,977
If my aura defense goes down,

169
00:09:37,010 --> 00:09:38,645
i’m done for!

170
00:09:38,679 --> 00:09:40,648
I’ve gotta end this...

171
00:09:40,681 --> 00:09:43,050
With my jajanken!

172
00:09:43,083 --> 00:09:46,753
( Yells )

173
00:09:46,787 --> 00:09:49,757
Knuckle: Bring it on!

174
00:09:49,790 --> 00:09:51,759
♪

175
00:10:00,667 --> 00:10:03,703
Killua: Knuckle definitely
has superior physical strength,

176
00:10:03,737 --> 00:10:06,273
but little by little,
gon’s adapting.

177
00:10:06,306 --> 00:10:09,943
By increasing the area
his aura covers,

178
00:10:09,977 --> 00:10:12,880
he reduces the damage
from miscalculations.

179
00:10:12,913 --> 00:10:15,616
He’s getting used
to knuckle’s speed,

180
00:10:15,649 --> 00:10:18,886
so surprise blows
aren’t hitting him anymore,

181
00:10:18,919 --> 00:10:20,888
but he’s running out of time.

182
00:10:20,921 --> 00:10:25,292
He doesn’t have much stamina
left to maintain his aura.

183
00:10:26,593 --> 00:10:28,095
Knuckle, on the other hand,

184
00:10:28,128 --> 00:10:31,898
is conserving his strength,
only attacking with basic blows.

185
00:10:32,933 --> 00:10:34,902
Unfortunately, jajanken

186
00:10:34,935 --> 00:10:38,305
requires a huge amount of aura
just to activate.

187
00:10:38,338 --> 00:10:41,308
Gon’s used up a lot of aura
in feints alone.

188
00:10:41,341 --> 00:10:44,377
He’s already used
his technique three times.

189
00:10:46,647 --> 00:10:50,117
They started fighting
20 minutes ago.

190
00:10:50,150 --> 00:10:52,919
If he uses jajanken again,

191
00:10:52,953 --> 00:10:55,689
that means he’ll only have
a minute or two left

192
00:10:55,722 --> 00:10:57,624
to fight at full strength.

193
00:11:04,698 --> 00:11:06,700
( Gon panting )

194
00:11:10,904 --> 00:11:14,007
Knuckle: Gon, you told me

195
00:11:14,041 --> 00:11:16,143
that I should give it
everything i’ve got,

196
00:11:16,176 --> 00:11:19,079
but you’re still no match for me
as you are right now.

197
00:11:19,112 --> 00:11:20,680
♪

198
00:11:20,714 --> 00:11:22,082
You’re just--

199
00:11:22,115 --> 00:11:23,083
( killua gasps )

200
00:11:23,116 --> 00:11:26,653
Gon: Now show me...

201
00:11:26,687 --> 00:11:28,088
Rock!

202
00:11:28,121 --> 00:11:29,789
( Killua gasps )

203
00:11:29,823 --> 00:11:31,692
Why?

204
00:11:33,694 --> 00:11:37,298
Wait. What the hell
is he thinking?

205
00:11:37,331 --> 00:11:39,333
( Knuckle gasping )

206
00:11:45,138 --> 00:11:47,941
Gon: Now show me...

207
00:11:47,975 --> 00:11:49,910
Rock!

208
00:11:49,943 --> 00:11:52,512
( Knuckle gasps )

209
00:11:52,546 --> 00:11:55,249
Killua: Knuckle
doesn’t have a shot

210
00:11:55,282 --> 00:11:58,519
and hasn’t taken damage,
so why from that far?

211
00:11:58,552 --> 00:12:01,922
It doesn’t even look
like he’s gonna hit him.

212
00:12:06,426 --> 00:12:09,696
Knuckle: This will definitely be
gon’s final attack.

213
00:12:09,730 --> 00:12:12,433
It’ll all end right here.

214
00:12:12,466 --> 00:12:15,970
Gon: Jan Ken...

215
00:12:16,003 --> 00:12:19,440
Paper!

216
00:12:20,874 --> 00:12:22,442
( Both gasp )

217
00:12:22,476 --> 00:12:24,578
♪

218
00:12:24,611 --> 00:12:26,646
Knuckle: An emission attack?

219
00:12:26,680 --> 00:12:28,015
I wasn’t expecting that,

220
00:12:28,048 --> 00:12:30,050
and it’s weaker than his rock.

221
00:12:31,852 --> 00:12:34,455
You’re an enhancer,
no doubt about it.

222
00:12:34,488 --> 00:12:38,459
Paper’s an emission,
so it’s much weaker,

223
00:12:38,492 --> 00:12:41,462
no speed, no punch.

224
00:12:41,495 --> 00:12:43,764
There can’t possibly be
a gimmick

225
00:12:43,797 --> 00:12:45,866
in such a low-level attack!

226
00:12:45,899 --> 00:12:49,069
I’ll deflect it, and it’s over!

227
00:12:49,102 --> 00:12:52,005
Yah!

228
00:12:52,039 --> 00:12:53,641
Gon: All right. Round two!

229
00:12:54,775 --> 00:12:56,844
Knuckle: Round two?

230
00:12:57,878 --> 00:13:00,447
He used a decoy to ambush me?

231
00:13:00,480 --> 00:13:05,452
No good.
A jajanken combo attack!

232
00:13:05,485 --> 00:13:08,855
Gon: Rock!

233
00:13:08,889 --> 00:13:12,726
( Knuckle screams )

234
00:13:24,505 --> 00:13:27,475
( Gasping )

235
00:13:40,521 --> 00:13:42,123
He’s out cold.

236
00:13:42,155 --> 00:13:44,891
He spent all of his aura
before rock.

237
00:13:46,593 --> 00:13:50,363
If he hadn’t,
he would have beaten me.

238
00:13:50,397 --> 00:13:52,499
- ( Footsteps )
- Eh?

239
00:13:56,937 --> 00:14:00,574
Where the hell are you
going now, you fool?

240
00:14:00,607 --> 00:14:01,842
Killua: I’m heading back.

241
00:14:01,875 --> 00:14:04,111
Knuckle: Aren’t you
going to fight me?

242
00:14:04,144 --> 00:14:05,612
I’m ready for more.

243
00:14:05,646 --> 00:14:08,916
Killua: You can fight
with gon again tomorrow.

244
00:14:08,949 --> 00:14:12,553
The outcome
will probably be different.

245
00:14:12,586 --> 00:14:15,489
Then i’ll defeat shoot.

246
00:14:15,522 --> 00:14:19,626
Knuckle: You tell gon
that tomorrow,

247
00:14:19,660 --> 00:14:21,629
i’ll fight him for real!

248
00:14:21,662 --> 00:14:24,031
He’d better be ready to die!

249
00:14:24,064 --> 00:14:27,568
Killua: Sounds like you’re
trying to amp yourself up.

250
00:14:27,601 --> 00:14:29,636
Are you sure you can do it?

251
00:14:29,670 --> 00:14:32,473
Knuckle: Hell, yeah, you fool!

252
00:14:32,506 --> 00:14:34,842
- Killua: Tomorrow...
- Knuckle: Uh...

253
00:14:34,875 --> 00:14:38,078
Killua: You don’t
have to get serious,

254
00:14:38,111 --> 00:14:40,780
as long as you can win,

255
00:14:40,814 --> 00:14:44,184
but if you lose without fighting
at full strength,

256
00:14:44,218 --> 00:14:46,053
I won’t forgive you...

257
00:14:49,089 --> 00:14:51,959
Not for as long as I live.

258
00:14:54,862 --> 00:14:56,864
( Footsteps )

259
00:15:01,702 --> 00:15:04,738
Shoot: You are such a softie.
Do you know that?

260
00:15:04,771 --> 00:15:06,906
You don’t make
any sense at all.

261
00:15:06,940 --> 00:15:09,075
Why are you
helping the enemy improve,

262
00:15:09,109 --> 00:15:11,545
and furthermore,
why are you allowing them

263
00:15:11,578 --> 00:15:13,080
to criticize you for it?

264
00:15:13,113 --> 00:15:16,683
If you don’t want
to go to the ngl,

265
00:15:16,717 --> 00:15:19,086
you could
just give them your tile,

266
00:15:19,119 --> 00:15:23,090
though i’m almost certain
they would refuse it if you did.

267
00:15:23,123 --> 00:15:25,092
Knuckle: Bastard.

268
00:15:25,125 --> 00:15:27,060
You’re pretty damn cocky

269
00:15:27,094 --> 00:15:29,530
when you’re not
shaking in your boots, huh?

270
00:15:29,563 --> 00:15:31,899
In case you forgot,
it’s been a whole month,

271
00:15:31,932 --> 00:15:34,701
and all you’ve done
is stalk them!

272
00:15:34,735 --> 00:15:35,903
Shoot: I’ll do it.

273
00:15:35,936 --> 00:15:40,507
Tomorrow, I-I will fight them.

274
00:15:40,541 --> 00:15:41,976
( Knuckle groans )

275
00:15:45,179 --> 00:15:47,181
( Gon snoring )

276
00:15:52,553 --> 00:15:55,790
Bisky: Don’t worry.
I gave him a massage,

277
00:15:55,822 --> 00:15:59,526
so he’ll be able to fight
in top form tomorrow.

278
00:15:59,560 --> 00:16:01,829
Killua’s the real issue.

279
00:16:01,862 --> 00:16:04,098
I mean,
I really wasn’t expecting him

280
00:16:04,131 --> 00:16:07,735
to go the entire month
without fighting once.

281
00:16:08,969 --> 00:16:10,637
Killua!

282
00:16:10,671 --> 00:16:12,039
Killua: Eh? ( Gasps )

283
00:16:13,740 --> 00:16:15,842
Bisky: Prepare yourself
to fight me.

284
00:16:15,876 --> 00:16:17,878
( Muscles shifting )

285
00:16:21,281 --> 00:16:23,884
( Birds chirping )

286
00:16:23,917 --> 00:16:26,253
Gon: Whoa!
What happened to your face?!

287
00:16:26,286 --> 00:16:30,056
Killua: I was training
with bisky.

288
00:16:30,090 --> 00:16:32,826
Gon: Are you sure
she wasn’t torturing you?

289
00:16:32,860 --> 00:16:36,630
Killua: Anyway, what about you?
Are you feeling okay?

290
00:16:36,663 --> 00:16:38,165
Gon: Yeah, I feel fantastic!

291
00:16:38,198 --> 00:16:40,667
I used up all my aura,
so I expected

292
00:16:40,701 --> 00:16:44,138
that I would be pretty much
wiped out right now, but look!

293
00:16:44,171 --> 00:16:45,806
Kite: That gorilla--

294
00:16:45,839 --> 00:16:49,776
I mean the old hag’s massage
must have worked.

295
00:16:49,810 --> 00:16:51,779
- ( Sighs ) That was close.
- Gon: Huh?

296
00:16:51,812 --> 00:16:55,549
Bisky: Listen up! If you tell
anyone what happened yesterday,

297
00:16:55,582 --> 00:16:58,652
i’ll make your face
three times worse. You got it?

298
00:16:58,685 --> 00:17:00,921
( Laughs )

299
00:17:00,954 --> 00:17:03,790
Killua: She really
meant it, too.

300
00:17:05,192 --> 00:17:09,797
Bisky: Well? Are you able
to see your weakness now?

301
00:17:09,830 --> 00:17:11,999
( Killua panting )

302
00:17:12,032 --> 00:17:14,801
Bisky: You give up
far too easily,

303
00:17:14,835 --> 00:17:18,272
and you’re
much too cautious in combat.

304
00:17:18,305 --> 00:17:22,810
I’d even go so far as to say
you underestimate yourself.

305
00:17:22,843 --> 00:17:25,346
Every time you face an opponent

306
00:17:25,379 --> 00:17:27,348
you perceive
is stronger than you,

307
00:17:27,381 --> 00:17:31,318
you fight to escape, not to win!

308
00:17:31,351 --> 00:17:35,021
♪

309
00:17:35,055 --> 00:17:38,825
It’s a problem, but I realize
it’s not one of your making.

310
00:17:38,859 --> 00:17:42,196
It’s the fault of whoever
taught you how to fight.

311
00:17:49,670 --> 00:17:52,373
A habit that’s as deeply
ingrained as this one is

312
00:17:52,406 --> 00:17:55,276
will be difficult to break,

313
00:17:55,309 --> 00:17:58,045
but one thing is for sure.

314
00:18:00,414 --> 00:18:04,051
One day, you will
leave gon behind to die.

315
00:18:04,084 --> 00:18:06,086
♪

316
00:18:09,790 --> 00:18:11,659
Combat ability can change

317
00:18:11,692 --> 00:18:14,828
depending on internal
and external conditions.

318
00:18:14,862 --> 00:18:17,098
For example,
"c" on his best day,

319
00:18:17,130 --> 00:18:19,165
can beat "d" on his worst.

320
00:18:19,199 --> 00:18:23,770
"A," "b," and "c" can,
under the proper circumstances,

321
00:18:23,804 --> 00:18:27,041
beat "d," in spite
of the large power differential.

322
00:18:27,074 --> 00:18:28,042
But that’s them.

323
00:18:28,075 --> 00:18:29,777
You, on the other hand,

324
00:18:29,810 --> 00:18:32,413
assume the enemy is
always at their best.

325
00:18:32,446 --> 00:18:36,050
You adopt the worst-case
scenario every time.

326
00:18:38,986 --> 00:18:41,889
Even against enemies
of equal strength,

327
00:18:41,922 --> 00:18:43,323
you think, "he’s tough,"

328
00:18:43,357 --> 00:18:46,026
or, "it’d be dangerous
if he did this."

329
00:18:46,059 --> 00:18:50,130
Then you give up at even
the slightest disadvantage.

330
00:18:50,163 --> 00:18:52,265
You would never make
the smallest attempt

331
00:18:52,299 --> 00:18:53,801
to pull out a victory.

332
00:18:53,834 --> 00:18:58,806
You would run,
because you think like a loser.

333
00:18:58,839 --> 00:19:01,675
You need to overcome
this bad habit right away.

334
00:19:01,708 --> 00:19:03,677
Get way out
of your comfort zone,

335
00:19:03,710 --> 00:19:05,445
and take a big risk for once

336
00:19:05,479 --> 00:19:07,815
by challenging
someone more powerful,

337
00:19:07,848 --> 00:19:10,351
and tomorrow...

338
00:19:11,752 --> 00:19:14,221
If you can’t defeat shoot,

339
00:19:14,254 --> 00:19:17,357
you must stay out of gon’s life.

340
00:19:20,260 --> 00:19:21,995
( Killua sighs )

341
00:19:22,029 --> 00:19:24,832
Gon: Okay!
I’m gonna win this time!

342
00:19:24,865 --> 00:19:26,834
♪

343
00:19:26,867 --> 00:19:28,836
( Grunts )

344
00:19:39,880 --> 00:19:40,914
Killua: Let’s go.

345
00:19:40,948 --> 00:19:42,450
Gon: Okay.

346
00:19:51,258 --> 00:19:53,494
Bisky: Killua’s
overly cautious style

347
00:19:53,527 --> 00:19:55,929
can only come from one place.

348
00:19:55,963 --> 00:19:58,866
It’s the product
of a smothering kind of love...

349
00:20:01,368 --> 00:20:05,906
A love that’s abnormal,
obsessive, and distorted.

350
00:20:05,939 --> 00:20:08,408
In the end, it becomes a burden,

351
00:20:08,442 --> 00:20:10,878
smothering him
under its own weight.

352
00:20:10,911 --> 00:20:12,246
It’s a curse that will take

353
00:20:12,279 --> 00:20:15,816
an enormous amount
of effort to break.

354
00:20:17,918 --> 00:20:19,286
( Door creaks )

355
00:20:19,319 --> 00:20:22,355
( Nen whooshing )

356
00:20:29,329 --> 00:20:31,898
As to who
will emerge victorious,

357
00:20:31,932 --> 00:20:34,568
I honestly don’t know.

358
00:20:36,136 --> 00:20:37,304
All right...

359
00:20:39,106 --> 00:20:41,308
Better make a run for it!
( Laughs )

360
00:20:41,341 --> 00:20:44,311
♪

361
00:21:09,136 --> 00:21:11,405
Knuckle: So whoever loses...

362
00:21:11,438 --> 00:21:13,607
Gon: ...Gives up their tile
to the winner.

363
00:21:15,976 --> 00:21:19,246
Narrator: Gon and knuckle,
killua and shoot,

364
00:21:19,279 --> 00:21:23,183
their long-awaited
final battle begins.

365
00:21:25,085 --> 00:21:26,053
♪

366
00:21:26,086 --> 00:21:28,088
( Singing in Japanese )

